"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/867492","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-03-27","<p>The Inspection Programme is determined by Ofsted and is not pre-communicated to the Department.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2018-03-27T15:07:21.12Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/867492/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/867492/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/867492/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-03-20","Army Foundation College: Inspections","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, when the next Ofsted inspection of AFC Harrogate is due to take place.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","133467"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/867493","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-03-28","<p>Training establishments are subject to a range of assurance inspections. The Welfare and Duty of Care of all our personnel remains a top priority with continuous activities ongoing to ensure its robust delivery.</p><p>AFC Harrogate has been internally audited by the Army for welfare and duty of care issues since the Ofsted inspection in 2012. It may be of interest to the Honourable Member that Ofsted carried out an inspection of AFC Harrogate in October 2017, the final report for which will be published in the summer 2018.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2018-03-28T15:55:09.793Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/867493/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/867493/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/867493/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-03-20","Army Foundation College: Inspections","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, for what reasons AFC Harrogate has not been inspected for welfare and duty of care issues since 2012.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","133468"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/867494","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-03-26","<p>A non-requesting partner cannot reverse a split payment arrangement. The arrangement can be reviewed if the applicant and/or their partner provide further information via their online account, face to face with a Work Coach or over the phone. However, the arrangement will only be reversed if the Secretary of State is satisfied that it is in the best interest of the household.</p><p>To help ensure people requesting reviews are acting in the interests of their household, Universal Credit agents will collect as much information as possible from the claimants. This information will include details of the mismanagement of welfare support, its effect on individual members of the household and reasons for no longer making split payments.</p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse",,"2018-03-26T16:31:30.59Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/867494/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/867494/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/867494/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-03-20","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, with reference to the Universal Credit split payment arrangement related to domestic violence cases, whether non-requesting partners are able to reverse a request via (a) their online account or (b) Jobcentre Plus.","false","Biography information for Heidi Allen","South Cambridgeshire","Heidi Allen","133469"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/867495","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-03-27","<p>Army Foundation College (AFC) Harrogate carries out internal audits in addition to Ofsted and Departmental inspections.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2018-03-27T15:06:47.01Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/867495/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/867495/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/867495/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-03-20","Army Foundation College: Inspections","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether AFC Harrogate conducts internal inspections of its own education, welfare and duty of care standards.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","133470"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/867496","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-03-27","<p>Army Foundation College (AFC) Harrogate was inspected using the &quot;<em>Common Inspection Framework</em>&quot; (full title: &quot;<em>The revised Common Inspection Framework for further education and skills 2012: contextualised for use in the inspection of welfare and duty of care in Armed Services' training</em>&quot;). This framework is used for all Ofsted inspections of Welfare and Duty of Care in Defence initial training establishments. A copy of the framework is attached.</p><p>The policy on selecting establishments for inspection is set out in Part 1 (Section 3) of the attached Ofsted framework. The Inspection Programme is determined by Ofsted and is not pre-communicated to the Department.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","133605","2018-03-27T15:03:19.923Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/867496/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/867496/answer","MOD inspection framework 2012 v6 doc revison april 2015 (1).doc","MOD inspection framework 2012 v6 doc revison april 2015 (1).doc","133471 - MOD Inspection Framework","133471 - MOD Inspection Framework","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/867496/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-03-20","Army Foundation College: Inspections","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what inspection framework Ofsted uses to inspect AFC Harrogate.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","133471"
